FBIS4-46242 "jptot023__l94028" JPRS-TOT-94-023-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 2 June 1994 LATIN AMERICA PERU State of Emergency in Several Puno Provinces Extended State of Emergency in Several Puno Provinces Extended PY0206224094 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 2 Jun 94 PY0206224094 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network Spanish BFN [Text] The state of emergency has been extended until August in the Provinces of Carabaya, Sandia, and (San Antonio de Cupina), Puno Department, on the request of the Armed Forces. The purpose of the extension of the state of emergency, which includes the suspension of individual rights, is to assist the countersubversive operations being carried out by the Army in that part of the country.
